{
  "texts": [
    "As a result, large-scale evaluations were necessarily curtailed, particularly for the 13B model, which was only trained for 800 steps.",
    "The elevated final loss (1.289) in this setting is mainly due to adapter underfitting and insufficient optimization cycles.",
    "Still, this run confirms that DRaFT-Q remains stable and effective even under tight compute budgets, and can be pushed further with access to more powerful infrastructure.Another limitation is the narrow scope of the datasets.",
    "This study focused primarily on reasoning-heavy tasks such as CommonsenseQA, OpenBookQA, GSM8K, and dialogue datasets such as OpenAssistant, OpenHermes, and Ul-traChat.",
    "Although these benchmarks demonstrate the strengths of DRaFT-Q in multistep reasoning, future work must explore its effectiveness in broader domains such as summarization, document classification, answering questions on knowledge graphs and understanding biomedical text."
  ]
}